    "causal_summary": "The framework supports three runtimes — OpenCode, Claude Code, Codex — whose `agents/` directories are real, separate folders (unlike `commands`/`skills`/`specs`, which are symlinks to `.opencode/`). The native `@deep-context` analyzer agent existed only as `.opencode/agents/deep-context.md`; it was the only one of 13 agents missing its `.claude/agents/*.md` and `.codex/agents/*.toml` mirrors. Because `/deep:start-context-loop` dispatches native seats **by name** from the host runtime's own `agents/` dir, running the loop from Claude Code or Codex silently lost the two native seats from the default pool, degrading the cross-executor agreement signal.",
